NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There are 2 choices. a 2S cuebid shows a limit raise or better. However, I play that 2S promises 4 card support, and she does not have 4 card support, and in fact the 3 card support is kind of mangy. The choice I prefer is 2C bid (they are not playing 2/1).  But even if they were playing 2/1, 2C is not a game force in a competitive auction. It has the same meaning as in SAYC - 10+ points, usually 5+ clubs, and forcing 1 round.I play new suit is forcing, even over an overcall. East can then bid 3@H later.|
